{
  "texts": [
    "Afterwards, the processed features are concatenated and passed through a shared 1 × 1 convolutional transformation function T 1, followed by an activation operation, resulting in a feature map of size 1 × (W + H) × C.",
    "The specific operation is as follows:",
    "In the equation, σ represents the non-linear activation operation, and leaky ReLU is used in this case.",
    "f represents the feature map obtained after the previous stage processing.",
    "Next, the feature map f is split along the W dimension into two independent tensors, f w ∈ R 1×W×C and f h ∈ R H×1×C, which are aligned in dimension using a 1 × 1 convolution."
  ]
}